  "prompt": "Do wrestlers have to stretch before they workout?",
  "response": "Yes, wrestlers, like other athletes, are typically advised to stretch before their workout or training sessions. Stretching helps to warm up the muscles, increase flexibility, and reduce the risk of injury. It also prepares the body for the various physical demands that will be placed on it during the workout, including strength training, cardio exercises, and specific wrestling techniques. Incorporating both dynamic stretching before exercises and static stretching afterwards can be beneficial for overall performance and muscle recovery.",
